$PINS imagine Pins will reach the same market cap as Snap, translating in a stock price of $80+, I think this is doable within a year if they beat earnings again with huge numbers. With only one week left, I hope Pins doesn't run up to quickly though, because if numbers are in line with the Streets expectations, there's a chance of a selloff back to the low 40s. Expectations are very high now after $SNAP beat. So to justify a move way higher, the earnings need to be excellent.

links.title: Why These Social Media Stocks Are Trading Higher Today
links.description: Shares of several social media companies are trading higher in sympathy with Snap Inc. (NYSE: SNAP) after the company reported strong third-quarter earnings results. Snap also reported daily active users grew by 18% year-over-year. Twitter, Inc. (NYSE: TWTR) was trading up 8.33% at $50.21 per share on Wednesday at the time of publication.

links.title: Pinterest jumps as analysts say buy after Snap earnings beat
links.description: Shares of Pinterest ( PINS) are on the rise on Wednesday after both Bank of America analyst Justin Post and Goldman Sachs analyst Heath Terry upgraded the stock to Buy following Snap's ( SNAP) earnings beat. Post reads the latter's better than expected quarterly results as another sign of a strong online advertising rebound, an opinion shared by his peer at Goldman.
